\pard\f0\fs28  {\b O. pyrenaica} (Sennen) Sennen ex Sirj.,{\i  Publ. Fac. Sci. Univ. Masaryk }{\b 56}: 135 (1925), from the Pyrenees, is a rare taxon of somewhat uncertain affinities related to {\b 15 b} and {\b 17}. It is a dwarf (up to 12 cm) sparsely pubescent perennial, with leaflets 2-4 × 1·5-2·5 mm; calyx-teeth about as long as tube, with a few short hairs on the margin; corolla 8-10 mm; legume with 4-6 teeth up to 1·5 mm on the margin.
\par

