\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. O. reuteri} Leresche in Leresche & Levier,{\i  Deux Excurs. Bot.} 73 (1880). Pubescent perennial up to 30 cm, with appressed hairs. Leaflets 7-11 pairs, 3-7 × 1·5-2·5 mm, linear to obovate. Calyx pubescent, exceeding the keel, the teeth 1·5-2·5 times as long as tube; corolla 7-9 mm, Legume 6-7 mm, pubescent; sides toothed; margin with 6-7 teeth up to 2 mm. •{\i  N. Spain.} Hs.
