\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. O. montana} DC. in Lam. & DC.,{\i  Fl. Fr.} ed. 3,{\b  4}: 611 (1805). Subglabrous or sparsely pubescent perennial up to 50 cm. Leaflets 5-8 pairs, elliptical or ovate to oblong. Calyx sparsely pubescent, the hairs appressed or erecto-patent; corolla (8-)10-14 mm, pink, usually with purple veins. Legume pubescent; sides toothed or unarmed; margin with 4-8 teeth.{\i  Mountains of C. Europe, Italy and the Balkan peninsula; doubtfully in the Pyrenees.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He It Ju Po Rm.
